Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_enable_..._compatibility(25.10)  timing_enable_..._compatibility(25.10)

Name
       timing_enable_get_objects_regexp_compatibility

Syntax
       timing_enable_get_objects_regexp_compatibility {true | false}

       Default: false

       Defines  the  pattern search scope to boundaries deduced from hierarchy
       separation characters specified in the search pattern.

       When set to false, the commands with -regexp parameter will  search  at
       the top level only (unless used with the -hier parameter).

       When set to true, the commands will search the specified pattern within
       the hierarchies based upon the given pattern hierarchy (similar to pat-
       tern  search  without  the -regexp parameter). The -hier along with the
       -regexp parameter shows the same behavior similar to when  the  command
       is used without the -regexp option - only the leaf level object name is
       compared to the pattern match.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

       Examples

       Command behavior when this global variable is false:

       get_pins -regexp seg2/.*/QN

       **WARN:  (TCLCMD-513): The software could not find a matching object of
       the specified type for the pattern '.*/.*'

       **ERROR: (TCLCMD-917): Cannot find 'pins' that match 'seg2/.*.*/QN'

       get_pins -regexp seg2/.*/QN -hier

       seg2/u3/QN seg2/u9/QN seg2/u14/QN

       get_pins -regexp .*/QN -hier

       seg1/u3/QN seg1/u9/QN  seg1/u14/QN  seg2/u3/QN  seg2/u9/QN  seg2/u14/QN
       seg3/u3/QN seg3/u9/QN seg3/u14/QN u2/QN u5/QN u8/QN

       Command behavior when this global variable is true:

       get_pins -regexp seg2/.*/QN

       seg2/u3/QN seg2/u9/QN seg2/u14/QN

       get_pins -regexp seg2/.*/QN -hier

       **WARN:  (TCLCMD-513): The software could not find a matching object of
       the specified type for the pattern '.*/.*'

       **ERROR:    (TCLCMD-917):    Cannot    find    'pins'    that     match
       'seg2/.*.*.*.*.*/QN'

       get_pins -regexp .*/QN -hier

       seg1/u3/QN  seg1/u9/QN  seg1/u14/QN  seg2/u3/QN  seg2/u9/QN seg2/u14/QN
       seg3/u3/QN seg3/u9/QN seg3/u14/QN u2/QN u5/QN u8/QN

